data.title: Ben Te'o will make his Leinster debut for the A team this weekend
data.meta_description: The Australian centre will get his first run out against Carmarthen Quins.
data.text:
LEINSTER NAMED THEIR team to face Castres earlier today and while Luke Fitzgerald was handed his first start in seven months there was still no place for Antipodean import Ben Te’o as he makes the switch from rugby league.

Instead, Te’o will wear the 13 jersey for Girvan Dempsey’s A team away to Carmarthen Quins tomorrow (kick-off 2.30). Te’o's array of skills has many people excited at what he can bring to the Leinster squad as they search for a long-term replacement for Brian O’Driscoll at outside centre. Te’o is partnered in midfield by Steve Crosbie, who also captains the side.
